cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it describes a system that uses deep convolutional neural networks to automatically filter clinically significant findings from CT head scans. It also mentions the use of approximately 3.5 million CT head images to train the CNNs, which is a common approach in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses deep learning techniques to train the CNNs. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the system is designed to mimic the decision-making process of radiologists. 

Human-computer interaction (cs.HC) is also a possible sub-category as the system is intended to reduce the workload of human radiologists. 

Finally, information retrieval (cs.IR) is a possible sub-category as the system involves filtering and reporting on high-confidence studies.
